Using Jira & Fisheye, if a developer commits with "abc-123 #comment Dummy comment.", in issue ABC-123 a comment from that developer will show up with the text "Dummy comment.". There's been requests from users (who may or may not have access to the "Source" tab in Jira) to have comments coming from Fisheye/commits be marked in some what so they know it's coming from a code commit. Can there be a prefix/suffix for comments from commits, or perhaps even link to the Fisheye commit at the end, so users can click directly on it in the comment and be brought to the full commit?

_Steps to replicate_
* Create an issue and include *15 comments* inside it (just as an example). Use the following comment:

{quote}
